  "lyric": "From the Florence sun to the Venice moon<br>\nOn and on I travel<br>\nWithout you, the road too long<br>\nAnd time is too slow<br>\n<br>\nThe sunflowers long for the light of the day<br>\nReaching for something that’s so far away<br>\nTo the sun they grow<br>\nTo the only one they know<br>\n<br>\nSave some sunshine, I ask my angels<br>\nFor someone waiting home<br>\nI've tasted Lucca, I've savoured Rome<br>\nBut I'd trade my freedom<br>\nFor you and me to be close<br>\n<br>\nYou are the water of my river<br>\nYou are the sun in my cathedral<br>\nYou are the youth of my fountain <br>\nYou are the knight of my castle<br>\n<br>\nQuestions are written in the stars<br>\nAnswers are hidden on the road<br>\nStories are the first victory of my quest<br>\nYou are the last piece of my puzzle",
